{
  "texts": [
    "In this examination, generative AI and technology more generally is seen as both deterministic and instrumentalsomething that is part of the larger schemata of eco-system of authorship.",
    "Our approach here is to treat authorship as practice, an autopoietic practice to be precise.",
    "This means that the system of authorship continuously recreates its elements and operations through internal processes while engaging with external influences.",
    "As we already stated, this perspective challenges traditional views of authorship as a relatively static entity, instead highlighting it as an evolving construct shaped by ongoing interactions between authors, their work, and the broader scientific and technological contexts.",
    "To illustrate the processes and practices of scientific authorship, including experimental approaches, theoretical approaches, and in social sciences, the practices we consider are delineated at the beginning of the drafting and the production of a first draft; through to revising, editing, and selfrevision, and the final revisions after peer review."
  ]
}